commit_message: pinned pysam version for compilation test
pinned pysam version for compilation test
pinned pysam version number. not compatible with 0.12 or above

Updated deprecated and removed pandas sort call

DataFrame.sort has been deprecated in favor of DataFrame.sort_values.
Pandas has removed the deprecated sort function. Updated EDD code to
call sort_values
made pysam version check a little more robust
Updated EDD to work with pysam v0.10.0
enabled email notifications on broken build
Added travis build status to README.

(Fix for issue #3) Removed requirement that a read must be completely contained within chromosome.

Appearently, some aligners allow a partial alignment at the end of a chromosome.
There is no good reason to not allow this, so this behaviour is now allowed.
made pysam version check a warning instead of an error
fixed bug -> common_chroms intersection, not union
added missing descriptions to input check assertions
added dependency on specific pysam version and bumped edd minor version number
requires that informative bins must have ip and ctrl reads
fixed bug when no potential peaks are found during a gap penalty estimation step
fixed empty gap file bug and removed rpy2 dependency.
* setup.py: do not install edd-tools and bumped version number
added gzip flag to edd-tools log-ratio script
data frame was a view, had to make a copy. see previous commit.
had forgotten to make replacement of inf with nan inplace, fixed
made sure that log ratio bin sizes are always 10kb
fixed uncommon branch log variable name error
cleanup and renaming of variables and log messages
only loads all dependencies when the edd is being run (as opposed to -v and -h)
added option to save log ratios and made writing bin scores optional
added configuration file option and updated readme
Compute CI for p_hat using agresti_coull method in statsmodels.
fixed arguments order so multiple arguments are possible
initial support for merged analysis of multiple replicates
added better log message to golden_section_search

added requirement of min correlation between neighboring bins in
addition to bin NIB ratio.
gap penalty estimation uses golden section search
optimized estimation of gap penalty (run time only)
removed dead code. fixed workaround for multiprocessing keyboard interrupt bug (python bug that is)
debug version for guiding NSS search
fixed multiproc bug. will use same worker pool if multiple mc simulations are performed
added numpy include dirs to chrom_max_segments compile extension
added install time check of python version

Update README.md

wrote about gap file

breaking changes. small fix. todo when it break :)

it should now work on linux.. hopefully
fixed binary module names (included them into edd.path
added pyx library for reading bam files and counting reads per bin
tried to optimize score_function, but it values bin number too much!
added a better optimize search function
saved data from optimize cutoff to json file
added fraction of bins to plot

renamed package from enriched_domain_caller to edd

started working on new score function

seems to work, needs to guess a better value for % grade
log2-ratio set as default scoring. fixed multiproc random seed bug.
more modular, problems with assumption that mean(obs) + std(obs) cutoff makes sense.
